N1  - doi: 10.1086/261210
DO  - 10.1086/261210
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 108
EP  - 122
VL  - 92
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper develops the view that workers move into and out of the labor market because of changes in the perceived value of their market opportunities. A search model is combined with a matching model to yield movement of workers from job to job and into and out of employment.
AB  - This paper develops the view that workers move into and out of the labor market because of changes in the perceived value of their market opportunities. A search model is combined with a matching model to yield movement of workers from job to job and into and out of employment.
